==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puma
<hw>Pu"ma</hw> <pr>(p⟦umac⟧"m⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Peruv.
<ets>puma</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large American
carnivore (<spn>Felis concolor</spn>), found from Canada to Patagonia,
especially among the mountains. Its color is tawny, or brownish yellow,
without spots or stripes. Called also <altname>catamount</altname>,
<altname>cougar</altname>, <altname>American lion</altname>,
<altname>mountain lion</altname>, and <altname>panther</altname> or
<altname>painter</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pume</ent>⟦br⟧
